To further refine the search and potentially find a matching product, I will modify the parameters slightly. I will search for "Adidas black T-shirt" without the rating filter to see if we can locate any available products, and I will apply the rating filter only after retrieving the results.

Here’s the complete updated code:

```python
product = search_product(product_name="Adidas black T-shirt", brand="Adidas", category="clothing")
if product:
    # Filter products by rating manually
    filtered_products = {k: v for k, v in product.items() if v["rating"] > 4.5}
    if filtered_products:
        product_id = list(filtered_products.keys())[0]  # Get the first product ID
        cart_add_product(product_id=product_id, quantity=1)
        checkout_selected_cart(product_ids=[product_id], discount_code=None)
    else:
        raise ValueError("No suitable black Adidas T-shirt found with a rating higher than 4.5.")
else:
    raise ValueError("No products found for the query.")
```

